The paper discusses methods for verifying the input-output properties of deep neural networks, which are widely used in computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and control (cs.SY) applications. The methods discussed in the paper involve reachability analysis (cs.CR) and optimization, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY, and cs.CR.
